######################
initial login:
	username: root
	password: root
######################

Change root password:
	passwd
	new password: tropius
	re-type new password: tropius

Hostname alterations:
	echo TROPIUS > /etc/hostname
	sudo hostnamectl set-hostname TROPIUS

Add tropius user:
	useradd -m -s /bin/bash tropius
	passwd tropius
	new password: tropius
	re-type new password: tropius

Add guest user:
	useradd -m -s /bin/bash guest
	passwd guest
	new password: tropius
	re-type new password: tropius

Update pacman:
	pacman -Syu
	y to confirm
	pacman-db-upgrade
	pacman -S base-devel
	y to confirm

Set up sudo:
	pacman -S sudo
	y to confirm
	chmod +w /etc/sudoers
	echo 'tropius ALL=(ALL) ALL' >> /etc/sudoers
	chmod -w /etc/sudoers

#####################################################################
NOTE: From this point on we will be working under the tropius account
	username: tropius
	password: tropius
#####################################################################

Install yaourt:
	sudo pacman -S yajl
	Needed packages:
		package-query
		yaourt
	####################################################
	TODO: Add these to package and automate installation
	####################################################

Get some required packages:
	sudo pacman -S vim
	y to confirm
	sudo pacman -S ipython2
	y to confirm
	echo "alias ipython='ipython2'" >> ~/.bashrc
	sudo pacman -S python2-flask
	y to confirm
	sudo pacman -S postgresql
	y to confirm

Set up the postgresql database:
    sudo -i -u postgres
    initdb --locale en_US.UTF-8 -E UTF8 -D '/var/lib/postgres/data'
    exit
    sudo systemctl start postgresql
    sudo -i -u postgres
    createuser tropius -d -r
    exit
    createdb TROPIUS

Start the api:
    ###########################################################
    Have the TROPIUS package installed to /home/tropius/TROPIUS
    ###########################################################
    chmod +x ~/TROPIUS/api/app.py
    #####################################################
    Move the tropius.service file to /etc/systemd/service
    TODO: add the tropius.service file to the git repo
    #####################################################
    sudo systemctl enable tropius
    sudo systemctl start tropius

CONGRATS! We're at a working state!
